stories.title: County chief thrilled by NatWest Series opportunity
stories.summary:
Paul Millman, Chief Executive of Kent County Cricket, told reporter Andy

stories.title: Zimbabwe are transformed
stories.summary:
Far from resembling the dejected side they were after their recent Test
series with England, Zimbabwe now exude confidence in their play and almost a swagger in their demeanour as they dominate the NatWest Series

stories.title: Zimbabwe convincing in victory
stories.summary:
Zimbabwe, playing close to their true form, completed a highly convincing
70-run victory over a lethargic-looking West Indian team

stories.title: Zimbabwe move in on hat-trick of wins
stories.summary:
After 30 overs of the West Indian innings, Zimbabwe were on the verge of
another sensational victory

stories.title: Zimbabwe run spree
stories.summary:
Zimbabwe continued their run spree at the expense of a very tired-looking
West Indies team, totaling 256 for four in fine style off their 50 overs

stories.title: NatWest Series thriving thanks to Zimbabwe
stories.summary:
The NatWest Series is thriving, thanks to Zimbabwe's unexpected and spirited
start to the tournament
